en_680244_0	The newly-appointed Commandant, Combat Training School (CTS) at Ampara, Brigadier Vikum Liyanage assumed duties as the 39th Commandant on Friday (6) at the CTS premises in Ampara.
en_680244_1	The newly-appointed Commandant on arrival was honoured in a Guard Turnout and a ceremonial parade by the troops under command to the CTS.
en_680244_2	Afterwards, amid religious blessings, he left his signature for an official document and symbolized the acceptance of his new office.
en_680244_3	Later, he planted a Mango sapling in the premises as a symbol of memory and addressed the troops.
en_680244_4	Commanding Officer at the CTS, Officers and Other Ranks in Combat Training School Ampara were associated with the occasion.
